<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G/309: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-30T18:00:00-04:00">October 30, 1933—6
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 30—5:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>101. On Saturday efforts were made by Argentina to interest Chile,
                                Peru, and Brazil in backing a move to postpone the Conference for 3
                                months. Argentina urged postponement because of unliquidated Chaco,
                                Leticia, and Cuban situations. Chile is awaiting indication of
                                Peruvian attitude before taking any action but sees no gain in
                                delay.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>